name: Cut Outs
description:
Inspired by the works of Matisse in his late years, a master and inspiration, that even facing the difficulties of life, kept working on his art.

[Note: The concepts of Punctum and Studium originally called by Rolland Barthes directed to photography, can be applied to most visual compositions]

(Punctum: The part(s) of the image where the eye penetrates, where we tend to fix our stare, a detail or the missing of something)

(Studium: The parts of the image where our eyes can travel with ease, where we pass with our eyes, circulating and coming back to the Punctum)
